    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/mnh/sec/6038682681.html"></div>
        </div>
Interested candidates please respond with resume in body of email - <br>
Attachments will not be opened - <br>
<br>
Must have at least 2 years experience, NYS security license, good customer service skills, and a professional and authoritative presence -<br>
<br>
Description below - <br>
<br>
<br>
Position: SECURITY<br>
<br>
Reports To: All Managers and Trainers<br>
<br>
Job Summary:<br>
<br>
Responsible for all door policies and procedures and maintaining the security for the location, the staff and guests.<br>
<br>
Essential Functions<br>
<br>
Must be willing and able to:<br>
<br>
&#61623; Be New York State state, city, fire and/or police department certified.<br>
&#61623; Understand drinking laws.<br>
&#61623; Check for valid IDs.<br>
&#61623; Know and monitor the occupancy numbers.<br>
&#61623; Maintain an accurate head count of guests entering and exiting the location.<br>
&#61623; If an incident arises, be able to handle in the least confrontational manner.<br>
&#61623; If an incident arises, fill out completely all sections of an incident report.<br>
&#61623; Complete all sidework as assigned in a timely manner.<br>
&#61623; Perform calmly and effectively under pressure.<br>
&#61623; Relate to guests pleasantly and with good humor.<br>
&#61623; Communicate effectively with guests.<br>
&#61623; Assist with resolving conflicts in and around the location.<br>
&#61623; Master the walkie-talkie system within 2 days.<br>
&#61623; Communicate problems to management immediately.<br>
Must be willing and able to meet location requirements in the following:<br>
<br>
&#61623; Communicate effectively with co-workers.<br>
&#61623; Complete sidework when and as assigned.<br>
&#61623; Perform more than one task at a time.<br>
&#61623; Perform calmly and effectively under pressure.<br>
&#61623; Respond knowledgeably to questions about the location and menu.<br>
&#61623; Relate to guests pleasantly and with good humor.<br>
&#61623; Communicate with guest clearly, patiently, and courteously.<br>
&#61623; Communicate problems to management immediately.<br>
&#61623; Perform varied duties to ensure all aspects of service according to standing operating<br>
procedure.<br>
<br>
&#61623; Completely fill out all sections of an incident report<br>
Accountabilities<br>
<br>
Must be willing and able to:<br>
<br>
&#61623; Acquire and wear appropriate uniform or comply with dress code as prescribed in the training manual.<br>
&#61623; Maintain and clean uniform.<br>
&#61623; Maintain a well manicured appearance and persona that reflects the established image of<br>
the company.<br>
<br>
&#61623; Maintain clean and orderly work area throughout shift and leave it ready for business for the<br>
following shift.<br>
<br>
&#61623; Be an active team player with the location staff and (if applicable) hotel staff.<br>
&#61623; Be able to work at various locations when necessary.<br>
&#61623; Understand and follow supervisor's instructions.<br>
&#61623; Work under more than average stressful conditions.<br>
&#61623; Make appropriate judgment calls under stressful conditions.<br>
&#61623; Be able to diffuse conflict with the least amount of commotion.<br>
&#61623; Properly deal with celebrities and VIP guests according to MOC policies and procedures.<br>
&#61623; Use tact and appropriate judgment to smooth out difficulties with guests.<br>
&#61623; Promptly report guest problems to manager.<br>
&#61623; Read and be accountable for the information in the Employee Handbook and Safety and<br>
Training Manuals. Qualification Standards<br>
<br>
After training, must be able to pass an exam in English with 90% or better in each of the following:<br>
<br>
&#61623; Layout of location including table numbers and station numbers.<br>
&#61623; Information on all locations.<br>
&#61623; Individual orientation material including rules and philosophies, including reservation<br>
policies.<br>
<br>
&#61623; Door policies and procedures.<br>
Must be willing and able to:<br>
<br>
&#61623; Meet personal schedule requirements punctually.<br>
&#61623; Be warm, sincere, outgoing in personality.<br>
&#61623; Master English language sufficient to communicate effectively.<br>
&#61623; Provide a persona compatible with established image of the company.<br>
&#61623; Respond to the needs of difficult guests with patience and courtesy.<br>
&#61623; Accept constructive criticism.<br>
&#61623; Get along with co-workers.<br>
&#61623; Stand for long periods of time while on duty.<br>
&#61623; Attend to post<br>
&#61623; Do necessary walk-thrus as directed by the manager.<br>
&#61623; Work amidst noise in confined crowded space.<br>
&#61623; Assist in moving chairs/stools/tables when necessary.<br>
&#61623; Work nights, weekends and holidays.<br>
Rules The following are some rules that must be recognized:<br>
<br>
&#61623; May not take or give away any unauthorized company property including food or beverage.<br>
&#61623; May not eat or drink certain unauthorized items during a shift.<br>
&#61623; May not work under the influence of alcohol or other mood altering substances.<br>
&#61623; May not keep any unauthorized items in personal locker.<br>
&#61623; May not resort to any physical violence or harassing behavior.<br>
&#61623; May not hint, connive or question a guest regarding a gratuity.<br>
Failure to abide by these and other conditions of employment of the company set forth elsewhere can subject an employee to disciplinary action including termination.<br>
<br>
Accessibility varies by location.<br>
<br>
Job Type: Part-time<br>
<br>
Required education:<br>
<br>
High school or equivalent<br>
Required experience:<br>
<br>
Security: 2 years<br>
Required license or certification:<br>
<br>
NYS Security License    </section>

